API Key Guide

#description
This guide covers registering your application, managing credentials, and interactive testing on the Bankrate Developer platform. API keys authenticate your requests—treat them as sensitive secrets.

::

::page-section
## Overview

This guide walks through generating a key in the Developer Portal, trying an endpoint with **Try It!**, and rotating credentials when you need a new key. Copy keys once when they are shown and store them in a secret manager or similar—keys are not shown again after creation.

---

## Creating your API key

To integrate, generate a key through the Developer Portal.

1. Click **APIs** in the top navigation to view all APIs.
2. Click **View APIs** for the API you need a key for.
3. Click **Use this API**.
4. Click **+ New Application**.
5. **Label your application** with a descriptive name using the pattern `[Organization/Partner]-[API]` (for example, `Bankrate-ProductsAPI`).
6. **Add a description** explaining what the key will be used for.
7. Select **This is a team owned application**. Team-owned applications are strongly recommended.
8. Choose your team from the drop-down.
9. Click **Create and use API**.
10. On the next screen, **copy the credential** and save it somewhere safe (for example, a secret management tool). It is only shown once.
11. Add a custom name for your application and select **update credentials**.

---

## Testing your API key

1. Open **APIs** and select the API you created the key for.
2. Choose the endpoint you want to call (for example, Home Lending).
3. In the **Authentication** panel on the right, enter your API key.

